commitResults.messageTitle: Modify dummy values to prevent potential bugs
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, all dates 2001-01-01 counted as dummy values for mastery
check and consultation, and all empty strings counted as dummy values
for Telegram handle. This was done to make the Telegram, consultation,
and mastery check fields optional. Dummy values would not be displayed
on FRIDAY, so this was a potential bug.

Now, dummy values (renamed to empty values) are singular instances of
the respective classes, and hence no user inputs will conflict with
empty values. Tests have been added to ensure this behaviour.

However, this caused some bugs with loading in json data from storage,
as the empty instances would be saved with "empty" values, thus causing
them to fail the isValid check. A new method isValidOrEmpty was written
and used in the JsonAdaptedPerson class, whereby empty values would be
correctly replaced with empty instances in the Student object.

commitResults.messageTitle: Modify parseConsultation and parseMasteryCheck to catch date exceptions
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, LocalDateTimeParseExceptions were caught in
AddCommandParser, since the parse methods took in LocalDate objects as
argument. It was an inelegant solution as handling the exceptions in
the parse methods made more sense.

The methods have been modified to construct the LocalDate objects within
them so that they can catch the exceptions more naturally.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor person to student in various classes and files
Add ability to sort by criteria, in ascending or descending order
commitResults.messageBody:
New SortCommand and SortCommandParser classes have been created for this
feature. SortCommandParser takes one prefix as the criteria, and sorts
the SortCommand sorts the students in ascending or descending order. If
more than one prefix is provided, an exception will be thrown.

The Order class was created to follow the convention of having a Prefix
class.

Additionally, the method getFilteredStudentList has been refactored to
getStudentList as the ListView will display be a filtered list or a
sorted list depending on the command. The ListView will also refresh
every time a command is run, as I could not find any other way to
display the sorted list while also switching to a filtered list when
other commands are used.
